<subSubSection id="C30F0386B13DFF99FF55FA0FFE7EF881" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="120" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB13DFF98FF55FA0FFED8F95C" blockId="8.[166,1225,1514,1828]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">
D i a g n o s i s. This species can be recognized from the combination of face with facial carina; parafacial in profile 1.6× as wide as flagellomere 1 (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13DFF98FCDFF9EFFC45F99C" box="[849,963,1546,1572]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStart-2="Fig" captionStartId-0="9.[174,207,1641,1663]" captionStartId-1="7.[176,209,1342,1364]" captionStartId-2="11.[174,207,1680,1702]" captionTargetBox-0="[263,1145,180,1601]" captionTargetBox-1="[194,1203,178,1317]" captionTargetBox-2="[226,1185,174,1660]" captionTargetId-0="figure-5@9.[191,1208,174,1626]" captionTargetId-1="figure-181@7.[194,1204,174,1318]" captionTargetId-2="figure-5@11.[226,1188,174,1676]" captionTargetPageId-0="9" captionTargetPageId-1="7" captionTargetPageId-2="11" captionText-0="Fig. 4. Eupyrgota armipes, holotype ♀ (BMNH): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–5 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior; 5 — dorsal); 6 — fore femur and tibia, posterior view; 7 — mid femur, anterior view; 8 — fore trochanter; 9 — mid trochanter; 10 — wing; 11 — mesonotum and abdomen, dorsally; 12 — abdomen, posterior." captionText-1="Fig. 3. Eupyrgota angustifrons, holotype ♀ (BMNH): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–5 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior; 5 — dorsal); 6 — wing; 7 — mid femur and tibia, anterior; 8 — abdomen, left. Рис. 3. Eupyrgota angustifrons, голотип ♀ (BMNH): 1 — общий вид, слева; 2 — этикетки; 3–5 — голова (3 — слева;4 — спереди;5 — дорсально); 6 — крыло; 7 — среднее бедро и голень, спереди;8 — брюшко,слева." captionText-2="Fig. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, holotype ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) and holotype ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — habitus, dorsal; 5 — same, left; 2, 4 — labels; 6–7 — head (3 — anterior left view; 4 — dorsal); 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, dorsally. Рис. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, голотип ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) и голотип ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — общий вид, дорсально; 5 — same, слева; 2, 4 — этикетки; 6–7 — голова (3 — спереди слева view; 4 — дорсально); 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко,дорсально." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403939" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403937" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403941" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6403939/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6403937/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6403941/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">
fig. 4, 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13DFF98FC17F9EFFC45F99C" box="[921,963,1546,1572]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">3–5</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
), mesonotum and abdomen yellow with narrow brown or black marks or without them (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13DFF98FC32F9CFFC7FF9FC" box="[956,1017,1578,1604]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1641,1663]" captionTargetBox="[263,1145,180,1601]" captionTargetId="figure-5@9.[191,1208,174,1626]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Eupyrgota armipes, holotype ♀ (BMNH): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–5 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior; 5 — dorsal); 6 — fore femur and tibia, posterior view; 7 — mid femur, anterior view; 8 — fore trochanter; 9 — mid trochanter; 10 — wing; 11 — mesonotum and abdomen, dorsally; 12 — abdomen, posterior." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403939/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">fig. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13DFF98FB8DF9CFFBE2F9FC" box="[1027,1124,1578,1604]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13DFF98FB8DF9CFFB94F9FC" box="[1027,1042,1578,1604]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,1693,1715]" captionTargetBox="[185,1213,284,1656]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[185,1213,267,1656]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Eupyrgota aequalis, holotype ♀ (BMNH): 1 — habitus, dorsal; 2 — labels; 3–4 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior); 5 — fore coxa; 6 — mid femur; 7 — apex of oviscape. Рис. 1. Eupyrgota aequalis, голотип ♀ (BMNH): 1 — общий вид, дорсально; 2 — этикетки; 3–4 — голова (3 — слева; 4 — спереди); 5 — передний тазик; 6 — среднее бедро; 7 — вершина основного членика яйцеклада." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403933" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403933/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">1</figureCitation>
, 11, 12
</emphasis>
); scutellum with three pairs of long golden yellow setae; wing hyaline with gray apex and brownish radial fork; fore and mid trochanters with spinulose brown setulae (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13DFF98FC4FF98FFC7BF93C" box="[961,1021,1642,1668]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[176,209,1342,1364]" captionTargetBox="[194,1203,178,1317]" captionTargetId="figure-181@7.[194,1204,174,1318]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Eupyrgota angustifrons, holotype ♀ (BMNH): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–5 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior; 5 — dorsal); 6 — wing; 7 — mid femur and tibia, anterior; 8 — abdomen, left. Рис. 3. Eupyrgota angustifrons, голотип ♀ (BMNH): 1 — общий вид, слева; 2 — этикетки; 3–5 — голова (3 — слева;4 — спереди;5 — дорсально); 6 — крыло; 7 — среднее бедро и голень, спереди;8 — брюшко,слева." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403937" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403937/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13DFF98FB84F98FFBB5F93C" box="[1034,1075,1642,1668]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13DFF98FB84F98FFB9CF93C" box="[1034,1050,1642,1668]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[166,199,1588,1610]" captionTargetBox="[241,1189,195,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-8@16.[240,1189,195,1510]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 8. Eupyrgota flaviseta, holotype ♀ (1–6), paratypes ♀ (7–9) and} (10–14) (USNM): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–4 — head (3 — left; 4 — dorsal); 5 — fore femur and tibia, posterior view; 6 — mid femur, anterior view; 7 — epandrium, right; 8–9 — phallus glans, right and ventral; 10 — abdomen, dorsal; 11 — same, ventral, macerated in KOH; 12 — oviscape apex, ventrally; 13 — aculeus, ventral; 14 — spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403949/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">8</figureCitation>
, 9
</emphasis>
); fore femur thickened, with numerous strong suberect setae, mid femur with large oval femoral organ; setae in ventro-apical rows black, spurious; ventral hooks on oviscape strong; most setae brown to black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB13DFF98FF55F90FFE61F89C" blockId="8.[166,1225,1514,1828]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">
R e m a r k s. This species possesses all the characters of 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB13DFF98FCDCF90EFC4FF8BC" authorityName="Coquillett" authorityYear="1898" box="[850,969,1771,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13DFF98FCDCF90EFC4FF8BC" box="[850,969,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Eupyrgota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(s. str.), and I transfer it to the nominal subgenus.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6A0085B13CFF99FF20F98CFBFBF90C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403939" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6403939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403939/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="120" startId="9.[174,207,1641,1663]" targetBox="[263,1145,180,1601]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB13CFF99FF20F98CFBFBF90C" blockId="9.[174,1233,1640,1716]" pageId="9" pageNumber="120">
Fig. 4. 
